description: The included cushion can be used for lumbar support. Extra covers make it easy to give both your sofa and room a new look.
subjective_input: Clean and modern, but shallow and uncomfortable. A chair for looking at more than sitting in.

description: Extra covers make it easy to give both your sofa and room a new look.
subjective_input: We don't deny the Klippan is stylish, and the removable slipcover has come in handy. And with every year's catalog we continue to dream of buying a new slipcover as a fresh start. But all the slipcovers in Sweden won't make this sofa comfortable.

description: Easy to assemble. Lightweight and easy to move.
subjective_input: The best thing about this table is that you can bring it home on the subway, and it costs less than a (weekly) Metropass. A bland design that's cheaply finished and scratches easily. Great for hacking, though, so keep it for parts when you upgrade.

description: It?s easy to keep cords and cables out of sight but close at hand with the cable outlet at the back.
subjective_input: A boring design, with minimal space for storage and working. Belongs in a dorm room or on the curb.

description: Real wood veneer will make this bed age gracefully. Adjustable bed sides allow you to use mattresses of different thicknesses.
subjective_input: This is a decent enough bed once it's in place. But the act of building this bed with someone will be the true test of your relationship.  Choose wisely.

description: Solid pine; a natural material that ages beautifully. Seats 4.
subjective_input: The most basic chair in existence. Great if you like to DIY. Forever plain if you don't. But not particularly comfortable, stable or durable in either case.

description: Solid wood is a durable natural material which can be sanded and surface treated when required.
subjective_input: Sturdy, but hard and boring. About the same (in cost, utility, and design) as putting a door on a set of sawhorses.

description: Adjustable shelves can be arranged according to your needs. A simple unit can be enough storage for a limited space or the foundation for a larger storage solution if your needs change.

description: great dane. Hot atomic orange slubby weave is no slouch on bona fide living room chair inspired by our thing for Danish design. Barrel arms curve in a warm minimalist hug that looks great from all angles. Clean tapered back offsets deep comfy cushion. Love how the dark tuxedo legs play off the bright textured fabric?neat back angle on legs, too.
subjective_input: TBD, we'll report back when we've had a chance to check this out in person.

description: oui, we'll take it. So say you went to the Paris flea market and found this gem of a 50s sofa in an unbelievable blue that stops you in your tracks, but by the time you negotiated the euros and crated it back it'd still need refurbishing and oh, well, never mind, keep walking, but can't stop thinking about how cool it would be in your place. Find your vintage find anew at CB2: super long slim lines scaled just right for smaller spaces, cutback retro arms, low tufted back spanning double seat cushions?all avec a poly macro-weave in a totally tonal fresh hue: peacock blue on gunmetal stiletto legs. How easy was that?
subjective_input: It really is comfortable, and stylish, and not a bad pricepoint. Hard to test in store if you don't live in a major city, though.

A slim modern console by day, the Cocktail tranforms ingeniously to accommodate your guests when you need it. Worth checking out in store to see the full effect.
